{"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/EnablingAndDisabling","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/AddingComments","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/AssociatingBugs","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/LimitingExecutionTime","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Parallelization"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A complex package or project may contain hundreds or thousands of tests and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"suites. Some subset of those tests may share some common facet, such as being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"“critical” or “flaky”. The testing library includes a type of trait called"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"“tags” that can be added to tests to group and categorize them.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tags are different from test suites: test suites impose structure on test"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions at the source level, while tags provide semantic information for a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"test that can be shared with any number of other tests across test suites,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"source files, and even test targets.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Adding-tags","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Adding tags"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add a tag to a test, use the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Trait\/tags(_:)-505n9","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" trait. These traits"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"take sequences of tags as arguments, and those tags are then applied to the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"corresponding test at runtime. If they are applied to a test suite, then all"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tests in that suite inherit those tags."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The testing library does not assign any semantic meaning to any tags, nor does"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the presence or absence of tags affect how the testing library runs tests.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Tags themselves are instances of ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and can be expressed as string"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"literals directly in a test suite or test function’s declaration. Tags can also"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be expressed as named constants declared as static members of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". To","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"declare a named constant tag, use the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag()"},{"type":"text","text":" macro:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["extension Tag {","  @Tag static var legallyRequired: Self","}","","@Test(\"Vendor's license is valid\", .tags(\"critical\"), .tags(.legallyRequired))","func licenseValid() { ... }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If two tags with the same name ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"legallyRequired"},{"text":" in the above example) are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"declared in different files, modules, or other contexts, the testing library","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"treats them as equivalent.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If it is important for a tag to be distinguished from similar tags declared"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"elsewhere in a package or project (or its dependencies), use","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Reverse_domain_name_notation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to create a unique Swift symbol name for your tag:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["extension Tag {","  enum com_example_foodtruck {}","}","","extension Tag.com_example_foodtruck {","  @Tag static var extraSpecial: Self","}","","@Test","  \"Extra Special Sauce recipe is secret\",","  .tags(.com_example_foodtruck.extraSpecial)",")","func secretSauce() { ... }"]},{"level":3,"text":"Where tags can be declared","type":"heading","anchor":"Where-tags-can-be-declared"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Tags must always be declared as members of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" in an extension to that type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or in a type nested within "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Redeclaring a tag under a second name has no"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"effect and the additional name will not be recognized by the testing library."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The following example is unsupported:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension Tag {","  @Tag static var legallyRequired: Self \/\/ ✅ OK: declaring a new tag","","  static var requiredByLaw: Self { \/\/ ❌ ERROR: this tag name will not be","                                   \/\/ recognized at runtime","    legallyRequired","  }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a tag is declared as a name constant outside of an extension to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"type (for example, at the root of a file or in another unrelated type","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"declaration), it cannot be applied to test functions or test suites. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"following declarations are unsupported:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Tag let needsKetchup: Self \/\/ ❌ ERROR: tags must be declared in an extension","                            \/\/ to Tag","struct Food {","  @Tag var needsMustard: Self \/\/ ❌ ERROR: tags must be declared in an extension","                              \/\/ to Tag","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Customizing-a-tags-appearance","text":"Customizing a tag’s appearance","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, a tag does not appear in a test’s output when the test is run. It is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"possible to assign colors to tags defined in a package so that when the test is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"run, the tag is visible in its output."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add colors to tags, create a directory in your home directory named"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\".swift-testing\""},{"text":" and add a file named ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"tag-colors.json\""},{"text":" to it. This file","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"should contain a JSON object (a dictionary) whose keys are strings representing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tags and whose values represent tag colors.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On Windows, create the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\".swift-testing\""},{"type":"text","text":" directory in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"AppData\\Local\""},{"text":" directory inside your home directory instead of directly","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"inside it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tag colors can be represented using several formats:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The strings "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"red\""},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"orange\""},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"yellow\""},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"green\""},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"\"blue\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"purple\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", representing corresponding predefined instances of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", i.e."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag\/red"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag\/orange","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag\/yellow","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag\/green","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag\/blue","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag\/purple"},{"text":";","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A string of the form ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"#RRGGBB\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", containing a hexadecimal representation of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the color in a device-independent RGB color space; or","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"null","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" literal value, representing “no color.”"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, to set the color of the tag ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"critical\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to orange and the color of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the tag "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".legallyRequired"},{"type":"text","text":" to teal, the contents of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"tag-colors.json\""},{"type":"text","text":" can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be set to:"}]},{"code":["{","  \"critical\": \"orange\",","  \".legallyRequired\": \"#66FFCC\"","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Traits"]]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Trait\/tags(_:)-505n9","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Trait\/tags(_:)-yg0i","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag\/List","doc:\/\/org.swift.testing\/documentation\/Testing\/Tag()"]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/testing\/addingtags"]}],"kind":"article"